The stylesheet is currently **embedded directly** in your HTML document, inside the `<style>` block in the `<head>` section. This is sometimes called **internal CSS**.

Here’s where to find it:

```html
<head>
  ...
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      background-color: #0f0f11;
      color: #e0e0e0;
    }
    /* ... all other styles ... */
  </style>
</head>
```

---

### 🔧 If you want to separate it into its own CSS file:
You can copy everything from inside that `<style>` block and move it to a new file called `style.css`. Then, replace the `<style>` tag with this line:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
```

Let me know if you'd like me to go ahead and refactor it into an external stylesheet for you. It's easy to do — and makes future edits cleaner.
